headline: Fastenal price target lowered to $82 from $86 at Stifel
summary: Stifel lowered the firm’s price target on Fastenal (FAST) to $82 from $86 and keeps a Hold rating on the shares. Despite the Q4 revenue and AEBITDA miss, the shares traded up on optimism for higher growth and margin improvement in FY25. Even if the industrial macro environment remains depressed at current levels, Fastenal’s market share gains support mid-single digit revenue growth versus the slow 2.7% year-over-year growth reported in FY24, Stifel adds.
